                            <comment id="15025225" author="hachikuji" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 19:56:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It looks like when we updated the new consumer for persistence in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2017&quot; title=&quot;Persist Coordinator State for Coordinator Failover&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-2017&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-2017&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, we forgot to add handling for the request timeout error code. This code is possible when group metadata is written to the log if the write timeout expires before enough replicas have acknowledged it. I&apos;ve added a simple patch which checks for this error.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
